Ivan Guimarães Lins (born  June 16, 1945) is a Latin Grammy-winning Brazilian musician.
His first hit, "Madalena", was recorded by Elis Regina in 1970.
"Love Dance", a hit in 1989, is one of the most recorded songs in musical history.
"Love Dance", a hit in 1989, is one of the most recorded songs in musical history.

His songs have been covered by Patti Austin, David Benoit, George Benson, Michael Bublé, Eliane Elias, Ella Fitzgerald, Dave Grusin, Shirley Horn, Quincy Jones, Steve Kuhn, the Manhattan Transfer, Sérgio Mendes, Jane Monheit, Mark Murphy, Carmen McRae, Joe Pass, Lee Ritenour, Sarah Vaughan, Diane Schuur, Sting, Barbra Streisand, Take 6, Toots Thielemans, Dan Costa (musician) and Nancy Wilson.
He recorded in English for Reprise/Warner Bros. Records in the early 1990s.
One signature voicing he often employs in his own performances is the delayed addition of a ♯11 to a sus13 chord, or the delayed addition of a ♭9 to a sus13 chord.
